    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<ul>\n<li><p><strong><em>System properties</em></strong> are set on the Java command line using the <code>-Dpropertyname=value</code> syntax. They can also be added at runtime\nusing <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#setProperty-java.lang.String-java.lang.String-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>System.setProperty(String key, String value)</code></a> or via the various\n<a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Properties.html#load-java.io.InputStream-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>System.getProperties().load()</code></a> methods.<br>\nTo get a specific <em>system property</em> you can use <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#getProperty-java.lang.String-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>System.getProperty(String key)</code></a> or <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#getProperty-java.lang.String-java.lang.String-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>System.getProperty(String key, String def)</code></a>.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong><em>Environment variables</em></strong> are set in the OS, e.g. in Linux <code>export HOME=/Users/myusername</code> or on Windows <code>SET WINDIR=C:\\Windows</code> etc,\nand, unlike properties, may <em>not</em> be set at runtime.<br>\nTo get a specific <em>environment variable</em> you can use <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#getenv-java.lang.String-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>System.getenv(String name)</code></a>.</p></li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
